description:
&lt;p&gt;Want to work for a forward thinking, innovative organisation which puts local children at the centre of care?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Then why not join us at FCHC! We’re within easy reach of London, and Surrey offers a great balance between the buzz of a capital city and green countryside. We are looking for an enthusiastic and motivated Speech and Language Therapist, with a specialist interest in working with Preschool children (under 5 years of age) and their families, to join our supportive and creative team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work as a member of our friendly Early Years Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a challenging, varied and rewarding role; you will often be the first port of call for families and influential in supporting children to reach their full potential. Day to day you will be conducting assessments, writing reports and running therapy sessions (groups or individual) for a varied population of 0-5 year olds including children with Language disorders and delays, Social Communication Disorders, Speech difficulties, stammering, Down Syndrome, general delay and much more. You may work from a variety of settings (e.g. Clinics and GP practices, nurseries and patient’s homes).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of your role, you may also be involved in:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conducting Multi-disciplinary assessments with OT and physios&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Delivering training to parents, Health Visitors and nursery staff&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Liaising Education staff and contributing to EHCPs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our team also works with specialist caseloads for school aged children (aged 0-19) including children who stammer, children with an acquired brain injury and voice, so it may be possible to work with these groups, depending on your experience, interests and the needs of the service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We firmly believe that the best services for the children we serve come out of effectively training and supporting our Therapists. As such you will be supported by the following:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Regular supervision with your designated experienced Speech and Language Therapist&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A rolling programme of in-house training running across Surrey to update your knowledge and skills throughout the year (including ‘ASD diagnosis’, ‘Stammering’, ‘Using Parent Child Interaction’, ‘Writing EHCPs’, ‘Attention Autism’,  to name but a few).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Local journal club run by and for the SLT team within SE  Surrey&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working as part of a fantastic team, who share challenges and celebrate successes together&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Opportunities for multidisciplinary Clinical Supervision through FCHC networks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a team, we all need to be able to travel between sites across Surrey, therefore being a car driver and owner is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you think this role is for you then please make an application. If you want to find out more or have any questions about the role then please contact Becky Domingues.&lt;/p&gt;
